5000|$|One of {{the most}} {{important}} Australian hardwoods, E. obliqua is often sold with E. regnans (Mountain Ash) as [...] "Vic Ash" [...] or [...] "Tasmanian oak". It is slightly denser that E. regnans - estimates of density range from 720 kg/m3 to 830 kg/m3 - and harder too. The sapwood is pale brown, the heartwood light brown. It has an even texture, with <b>straight</b> <b>grains</b> sometimes interlocked, and well-defined rings. Gum veins are common.|$|R
