50|$|The wood is {{versatile}} and very useful for construction. It is light, with <b>straight</b> <b>grains,</b> {{and easy to}} work. It is used for {{a great variety of}} products, including telephone poles, railroad ties, bridges, boats, plywood and flooring, furniture, sports equipment, and musical instruments. It is easy to break down into chips, particle board, or pulp for paper. Its value has led to overexploitation of wild populations of the tree, and destruction of the forest ecosystems in which it grows. The Siberian tiger is resident in these pine forests, and preservation of this tree species is one step in the conservation of the tiger.|$|R
